PUH-BrianMartell Substrate Refill Equation — Understandable Explanation The “substrate refill” describes how the lattice restores density after a high-energy soliton (recoiling parton) depletes local ripple/photon density — the mechanical analog of the hydrodynamic wake in heavy-ion collisions. Simple picture: •  Depletion: Fast soliton drags lattice, creates low-density “hole”. •  Refill: Lattice tension acts as restoring force — ripples propagate inward, pushing density back to equilibrium. •  No new physics — pure continuity + elastic response. Formal equation: Continuity for photon density ρ with restoring term from tension κ (ρ_eq - ρ) and wave propagation. ∂ρ/∂t = D ∇²ρ + κ (ρ_eq - ρ) D diffusion-like from ripple speed, κ restoration rate from tension.
